intro: Cullen australasicum, commonly known as the Australian cullen, is a flowering plant native to southeastern Australia. It belongs to the family Fabaceae, which includes legumes and related plants. The plant is characterized by its compound leaves and small, pea-like flowers that range in color from white to pink. It typically grows in heathland and open woodlands, preferring well-drained soils. Cullen australasicum is often found in coastal areas and is adapted to a variety of environmental conditions.
